      <hedline>
        <hl1>Nader on Nader</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ralph Nader letter holds that Robert F Kennedy Jr's Aug 10 Op-Ed article criticizing him is 'deeply flawed'</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s Aug. 10 Op-Ed article taking me to task is deeply flawed by his erroneous premise and conclusion.</p>
        <p>First, I have indicated that there are ''few major differences'' between the two parties, not that there is ''no difference between Mr. Gore and Mr. Bush,'' as Mr. Kennedy wrote.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Robert F. Kennedy Jr.'s Aug. 10 Op-Ed article taking me to task is deeply flawed by his erroneous premise and conclusion.</p>
        <p>First, I have indicated that there are ''few major differences'' between the two parties, not that there is ''no difference between Mr. Gore and Mr. Bush,'' as Mr. Kennedy wrote.</p>
        <p>Second, I have never said that I would vote for George W. Bush, whom I have strongly criticized across the country, if forced to choose between him and Al Gore.  Indeed, I have never stated for whom I have ever voted or expect to vote since the 1960's, though it can be assumed that I will vote for the Green Party candidates this year.</p>
        <p>RALPH NADER  Washington, Aug. 10, 2000</p>
        <p>The writer is the Green Party candidate for president.</p>
      </block>
